    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к %iæx%i-%icæwæn%i ← *%ivahu%i-%ičyavuna%i „приятно-идущий“? ср.
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
            ><lang/><w>vahu-</w><gloss><q>хороший</q></gloss></mentioned> (отдельно в осетинском не
        сохранилось) и <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyu-</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w>čyav-</w><gloss><q>идти</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cæwyn"/>. <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>vahu-</w></mentioned>
        могло дать в осетинском %iæx%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8æx"/>]; для отпадения
        начального %iv%i ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævz-"/>(← %ivabza%i), <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_Acyrūxs"/> (← %iWacyruxs%i) и др. Ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ʒæbæx"/> (%iʒæb%i-%iæx%i) ‘хороший’.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to %iæx%i-%icæwæn%i ← *%ivahu%i-%ičyavuna%i "pleasantly
        walking"? cf. <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
            ><lang/><w>vahu-</w><gloss><q>good</q></gloss></mentioned> (it has not been preserved as
        a separate word) and <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyu-</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w>čyav-</w><gloss><q>go</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cæwyn"/>. <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>vahu-</w></mentioned>
        could give %iæx%i in Osetic [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8æx"/>]; for the loss of the
        initial %iv%i cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævz-"/>(← %ivabza%i), <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_Acyrūxs"/> (← %iWacyruxs%i) etc. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒæbæx"
        /> (%iʒæb%i-%iæx%i) ‘good’.</etym>
</entry>
